com.github.robtimus.stream

Class FutureValue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.robtimus.stream.FutureValue<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of CompletableFuture result.

    public final class FutureValue<T>
extends Object
    A class that allows filtering and mapping on CompletableFuture instances inside streams.

    In streams, applying operations such as Stream.filter(Predicate) immediately alter the state of the streams. When using streams of CompletableFuture, the result is not available when the stream operation is applied. This class is meant to help with that issue as far as possible. It does so by providing the most essential functionality using asynchronous mapping:

    • Filtering values. However, because the actual filtering is done asynchronously, instead of using Stream.filter(Predicate), Stream.map(Function) should be used in combination with filter(Predicate).
    • Transforming values, using a combination of Stream.map(Function) and map(Function).
    • Collecting values, using a combination of Stream.collect(Collector) and collect(Collector).
    • Running an action on values, using a combination of Stream.forEach(Consumer) and run(Consumer).

    Most other operations rely on the internal state of the stream to change. These operations should not be used after the first mapping to wrap(CompletableFuture). The only stream operations that can safely be used are Stream.map(Function) (both for mapping and filtering), Stream.forEach(Consumer) and Stream.collect(Collector). For other methods, if possible, use Stream.collect(Collector) as replacement. For instance, the following can be used as replacement for Stream.reduce(BinaryOperator) using Collectors.reducing(BinaryOperator): 

    
 CompletableFuture<Optional<Integer>> result = stream
         .map(FutureValue::wrap)
         .map(FutureValue.filter(i -> (i & 1) == 0))
         .collect(FutureValue.collect(reducing(Integer::sum));

    The following is a list of stream operations and their possible Collector replacements:

    Stream operations
    Stream operation Replacement
    Stream.toArray() Collectors.toList() and List.toArray()
    Stream.reduce(BinaryOperator) Collectors.reducing(BinaryOperator)
    Stream.reduce(Object, BinaryOperator) Collectors.reducing(Object, BinaryOperator)
    Stream.reduce(Object, BiFunction, BinaryOperator) Collectors.reducing(Object, Function, BinaryOperator)
    Note that this transforms values before accumulating them.
    Stream.min(Comparator) Collectors.minBy(Comparator)
    Stream.max(Comparator) Collectors.maxBy(Comparator)
    Stream.count() Collectors.counting()
    Stream.findAny() findAny()
    findAny(ExecutorService)
    Author:
    Rob Spoor

      • collect

        public static <T,A,R> Collector<FutureValue<T>,?,CompletableFuture<R>> collect(Collector<T,A,R> collector)
        Returns a Collector that accumulates FutureValue instances into a CompletableFuture. This method is similar to AdditionalCollectors.completableFutures(Collector). That method can be used if no filtering or mapping is needed on the CompletableFuture results.

      • run

        public static <T> Consumer<FutureValue<T>> run(Consumer<? super T> action)
        Returns a consumer that performs an action on FutureValue instances. This is usually used in a call to Stream.forEach(Consumer) or Stream.forEachOrdered(Consumer).

        Although this method can be used in a call to Stream.peek(Consumer), the result is unpredictable due to the asynchronous nature of CompletableFutures. The same goes for Stream.forEachOrdered(Consumer).

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of CompletableFuture result.
        Parameters:
        action - The action to perform for each CompletableFuture result. Note that the action is called asynchronously.
        Returns:
        A consumer that performs the given action on FutureValue instances asynchronously.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If the given action is null.

      • findAny

        public static <T> Collector<FutureValue<T>,?,CompletableFuture<Optional<T>>> findAny()
        Returns a Collector that returns any CompletableFuture result. To prevent waiting for more CompletableFutures to finish than necessary, this method will create another CompletableFuture using the ForkJoinPool.commonPool(). This will return as value the first available result, or throw the first available error.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of CompletableFuture result.
        Returns:
        A Collector that returns any CompletableFuture result.

      • findAny

        public static <T> Collector<FutureValue<T>,?,CompletableFuture<Optional<T>>> findAny(ExecutorService executor)
        Returns a Collector that returns any CompletableFuture result. To prevent waiting for more CompletableFutures to finish than necessary, this method will create another CompletableFuture. This will return as value the first available result, or throw the first available error.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of CompletableFuture result.
        Parameters:
        executor - The executor service to use for creating the new CompletableFuture.
        Returns:
        A Collector that returns any CompletableFuture result.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If the given executor service is null.
